description: Creates worlds using the specified template.

parameters.name: clientRequestToken
parameters.description: Unique, case-sensitive identifier that you provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: template
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (arn) of the world template describing the worlds you want to create.

parameters.name: worldCount
parameters.description: Information about the world count. floorplanCount (integer) --- The number of unique floorplans. interiorCountPerFloorplan (integer) --- The number of unique interiors per floorplan.

nested_params.name: interiorCountPerFloorplan
nested_params.description: The number of unique interiors per floorplan.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: A map that contains tag keys and tag values that are attached to the world generator job. (string) --- (string) ---

parameters.name: worldTags
parameters.description: A map that contains tag keys and tag values that are attached to the generated worlds. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the world generator job.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the world generator job.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The time, in milliseconds since the epoch, when the world generator job was created.

nested_items.name: failureCode
nested_items.description: The failure code of the world generator job if it failed:
